This paper proposes a deep learning solution for projector-camera systems, which involves computer vision (CV) and graphics (GR) techniques. The proposed method uses convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for learning and estimation, which falls under artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper addresses occlusion, which is a common problem in robotics (RO) and computer vision (CV) fields. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.GR, followed by cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.RO.
